1
00:01:36,813 --> 00:01:38,280
[PA BEEPS]

2
00:01:39,582 --> 00:01:41,106
PILOT [OVER PA]:
Ladies and gentlemen...

3
00:01:41,284 --> 00:01:43,275
...we are beginning our descent
into Berlin Tegel...

4
00:01:43,453 --> 00:01:47,583
...where local time is 8:30 a.m. And the
temperature is a cool minus four degrees.

5
00:01:47,757 --> 00:01:48,883
Morning.

6
00:01:49,726 --> 00:01:51,193
Did you sleep?

7
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:54,330
No. I'll sleep at the hotel.

8
00:01:55,465 --> 00:01:56,762
You'll do great.

9
00:01:58,501 --> 00:02:00,093
You always do.

10
00:02:03,273 --> 00:02:05,537
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN
OVER PA]

11
00:02:14,517 --> 00:02:16,041
What's the purpose of your visit?

12
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:20,053
We're here for a biotechnology summit.
I'm giving a presentation.

13
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:28,326
Mr. And Mrs. Harris, welcome to Berlin.

14
00:02:28,498 --> 00:02:30,193
MARTIN:
Danke schon.

15
00:02:31,634 --> 00:02:33,363
IMMIGRATION OFFICER:
Next, please.

16
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:35,933
"I'm giving a presentation"?

17
00:02:36,105 --> 00:02:38,471
Well, she asked.

18
00:02:41,878 --> 00:02:44,745
- Oof. Welcome to Berlin.
MAN: Taxi.

19
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:46,575
Taxi.

20
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:09,436
Martin, get in the car. Let him do that.

21
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,171
[GROANS]

22
00:03:13,476 --> 00:03:14,500
Oh, ya-ya.

23
00:03:25,889 --> 00:03:28,756
[DRIVER SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

24
00:03:51,347 --> 00:03:52,814
What do you think he's saying?

25
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:54,815
No idea.

26
00:04:01,257 --> 00:04:03,748
Look. Isabel Kronenberger is showing
here on Saturday.

27
00:04:03,927 --> 00:04:05,087
Oh, yeah.

28
00:04:05,261 --> 00:04:07,786
Remember when we saw her
in Chicago?

29
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:09,760
[CHUCKLING]
Yes.

30
00:04:12,268 --> 00:04:17,365
Why don't I meet you there on Saturday
after my lunch with Professor Bressler?

31
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,235
Yeah.

32
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,101
If you promise.

33
00:04:21,277 --> 00:04:22,801
I promise.

34
00:04:57,447 --> 00:04:59,972
- Welcome to the Hotel Adlon Kempinski.
MARTIN: Thank you.

35
00:05:00,149 --> 00:05:02,447
You check in, honey.
I'll take care of this.

36
00:05:02,618 --> 00:05:04,085
Have you stayed with us before?

37
00:05:04,253 --> 00:05:06,448
- First time in Berlin.
- First time in Berlin.

38
00:05:09,859 --> 00:05:12,555
RECEPTIONIST:
If there's anything else I can do for you...

39
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:13,991
How much do I owe you?

40
00:05:14,163 --> 00:05:15,255
DRIVER:
Thirty-seven, sir.

41
00:05:15,698 --> 00:05:18,690
Welcome to the Adlon Kempinski Berlin.
How may I help you, madam?

42
00:05:18,868 --> 00:05:21,996
- Dr. And Mrs. Harris, the Eisenhower suite.
- Of course.

43
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:25,003
MARTIN: Wait, wait.
- Everything okay, sir?

44
00:05:25,174 --> 00:05:27,972
- Is this everything from the taxi?
- Yes, sir.

45
00:05:30,346 --> 00:05:34,282
I'm afraid, Mrs. Harris, but the Eisenhower
suite may not be available right now.

46
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:35,849
What do you mean "not available"?

47
00:05:36,019 --> 00:05:37,611
There have been changes,
security reasons.

48
00:05:37,787 --> 00:05:38,811
[PHONE RINGING]

49
00:05:38,988 --> 00:05:40,683
But we confirmed two weeks ago.

50
00:05:40,857 --> 00:05:42,722
Would you allow me
to answer the phone?

51
00:05:42,892 --> 00:05:44,883
MARTIN:
I'll go to the airport. I'll be back, okay?

52
00:05:45,061 --> 00:05:46,995
[RECEPTIONIST SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

53
00:06:16,159 --> 00:06:17,854
Oh, please.

54
00:06:18,027 --> 00:06:20,291
Excuse me, driver?
Is there another route?

55
00:06:36,512 --> 00:06:37,536
Oh, come on.

56
00:06:49,725 --> 00:06:51,215
[TIRES SCREECHING]

57
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:55,190
- Look out!
- No!

58
00:06:56,265 --> 00:06:57,960
[GINA SCREAMS]

59
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,672
[GRUNTS]

60
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,835
[GRUNTING]

61
00:07:20,323 --> 00:07:21,654
[GASPING]

62
00:07:58,427 --> 00:07:59,860
[METAL CREAKING]

63
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,927
[SIREN APPROACHING]

64
00:08:08,104 --> 00:08:09,765
[CROWD SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

65
00:08:16,112 --> 00:08:18,046
[MAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

66
00:08:18,714 --> 00:08:21,444
Hello? Hello?

67
00:08:22,652 --> 00:08:23,778
[MUFFLED]
Can you hear me?

68
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,388
[EMTS SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

69
00:08:42,538 --> 00:08:44,472
[DEFIBRILLATOR CHARGING]

70
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:56,043
[DEFIBRILLATOR ZAPS]

71
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,190
[LIZ LAUGHING]

72
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,357
[LIZ MOANING]

73
00:09:21,744 --> 00:09:23,473
[RESPIRATOR PUMPING]

74
00:09:36,192 --> 00:09:39,218
[BOTH SPEAKING IN
MUFFLED GERMAN]

75
00:09:45,568 --> 00:09:47,035
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

76
00:10:04,887 --> 00:10:06,878
Dr. Farge?

77
00:10:09,058 --> 00:10:12,459
Dr. Farge. Dr. Farge.

78
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:18,766
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

79
00:10:25,308 --> 00:10:27,606
I don't speak German.

80
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,708
FARGE:
Are you English?

81
00:10:30,646 --> 00:10:32,113
American.

82
00:10:34,417 --> 00:10:36,647
You have been in an accident.

83
00:10:36,819 --> 00:10:38,480
Accident?

84
00:10:40,923 --> 00:10:43,050
Can you tell me your name?

85
00:10:45,127 --> 00:10:46,321
Your name.

86
00:10:46,495 --> 00:10:49,953
Martin. Martin Harris.

87
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,094
Dr. Martin Harris.

88
00:10:54,804 --> 00:10:55,930
Where's my wife, Liz?

89
00:10:58,541 --> 00:11:00,941
- Is she hurt? Is she hurt? Where is she?
- Calm down.

90
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:04,273
It's all right, Dr. Harris.
You were the only passenger.

91
00:11:04,447 --> 00:11:06,972
The taxi you were in went into the river.

92
00:11:07,149 --> 00:11:09,811
Your heart stopped for several minutes.

93
00:11:10,119 --> 00:11:14,453
It's Thursday, November 24th.
You have been in a coma for four days.

94
00:11:14,623 --> 00:11:19,651
Thanksgiving.
But my wife, she's in Berlin with me.

95
00:11:19,829 --> 00:11:21,854
Where is she? Why isn't she here?

96
00:11:22,031 --> 00:11:25,432
We couldn't find any identification
with you, Dr. Harris.

97
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:27,633
No, no, no.

98
00:11:27,803 --> 00:11:29,464
- Please, calm down.
MARTIN: Aah.

99
00:11:29,672 --> 00:11:33,267
Where can we reach your wife?
Does she have a cell phone?

100
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:35,876
Of course she has a cell phone. It's...

101
00:11:39,582 --> 00:11:40,810
Uh...

102
00:11:43,085 --> 00:11:44,177
I can't remember.

103
00:11:44,353 --> 00:11:48,221
Can you tell me what you do remember,
Martin?

104
00:11:49,358 --> 00:11:52,054
Bits and pieces. Arriving at the airport.

105
00:11:53,095 --> 00:11:55,586
Getting in a taxi with Liz...

106
00:11:56,832 --> 00:11:58,766
...but I don't know how I got here.

107
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:02,062
There are no rules with severe trauma
of this kind.

108
00:12:02,238 --> 00:12:04,172
Memories get lost or fractured.

109
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:06,501
Most of them return,
although it's unlikely...

110
00:12:06,675 --> 00:12:10,008
...you will ever fully recall the events
around your accident.

111
00:12:10,179 --> 00:12:12,977
In the meantime, let us see
if anyone has filed a report...

112
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:14,878
...looking for a Martin Harris, okay?

113
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:17,518
- Yes, yes, yes.
- Okay.

114
00:12:22,458 --> 00:12:24,085
[MAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN ON TV]

115
00:12:25,861 --> 00:12:28,261
ANNOUNCER: From London
with Kevin Spencer and Diana Bailey.

116
00:12:28,431 --> 00:12:30,422
Good evening.
Welcome to the BNI World News.

117
00:12:30,599 --> 00:12:32,157
Here are today's top stories.

118
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,358
The Prime Mini...

119
00:12:33,536 --> 00:12:34,560
[TURNS TV OFF]

120
00:12:34,737 --> 00:12:36,329
Clothes. For you.

121
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:40,732
MARTIN: Has anybody been
looking for me? My wife?

122
00:12:41,744 --> 00:12:42,836
Meine Frau?

123
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:10,630
[CHUCKLING]

124
00:13:15,978 --> 00:13:17,240
Come here, you.

125
00:13:23,252 --> 00:13:25,243
It's beautiful. Just beautiful.

126
00:13:25,421 --> 00:13:27,082
LIZ:
I'm glad you like it.

127
00:13:32,094 --> 00:13:34,119
She gave it to me as a gift.

128
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:37,363
In Paris. On our honeymoon.

129
00:13:57,553 --> 00:13:58,611
[CHUCKLES]

130
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:10,857
[SIGHS]

131
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:22,777
Prince Shada arrived in Berlin today for
this year's biotechnology global summit.

132
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:25,311
The personal attendance
of the flamboyant prince...

133
00:14:25,481 --> 00:14:29,008
...has fueled speculation that the summit,
now in its 10th year...

134
00:14:29,184 --> 00:14:32,551
...will witness the announcement
of a major scientific breakthrough.

135
00:14:32,721 --> 00:14:34,985
With the world's leading researchers
convening...

136
00:14:35,157 --> 00:14:37,591
...at the luxurious Hotel Adlon
in Central Berlin...

137
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,887
- Hotel Adlon.
...the field of biotechnology...

138
00:14:40,062 --> 00:14:42,724
...steps into the forefront
of the media spotlight.

139
00:14:42,898 --> 00:14:44,627
I'm here for the summit.

140
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:45,858
Nurse.

141
00:14:46,402 --> 00:14:48,233
You have to realize the risk.

142
00:14:48,404 --> 00:14:50,872
Doctor, I've been gone for four days.

143
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:54,237
My wife is out there in a city
she doesn't know. She'll be terrified.

144
00:14:54,410 --> 00:14:56,537
I need to find her.

145
00:14:59,415 --> 00:15:00,541
Sign this.

146
00:15:01,383 --> 00:15:03,908
It releases you from my care.

147
00:15:04,887 --> 00:15:06,184
And here's my card.

148
00:15:07,523 --> 00:15:11,482
Any nausea, dizziness, difficulty with
speech, you contact me immediately.

149
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:13,287
- Do you understand?
- Thank you.

150
00:15:27,977 --> 00:15:30,639
Welcome to the Hotel Adlon Kempinski.
How may I help you?

151
00:15:30,813 --> 00:15:34,408
Yes, hi. I'm a guest of the hotel.
I lost my room key. I need a new one.

152
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:37,017
- What room are you staying in?
- The Eisenhower suite.

153
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:40,349
- And may I have your name?
- Martin Harris. Dr. Martin Harris.

154
00:15:41,924 --> 00:15:44,552
And may I please see some ID,
Mr. Harris?

155
00:15:44,727 --> 00:15:48,424
There's been a situation.
I've lost my passport.

156
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:50,855
I'm going to need some ID, sir.

157
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:54,161
If you get someone to escort me
to my room, I can prove it.

158
00:15:54,336 --> 00:15:56,065
Just give me a moment.

159
00:16:04,947 --> 00:16:08,110
[MAN AND RECEPTIONIST SPEAKING
IN GERMAN ON PHONE]

160
00:16:19,962 --> 00:16:21,930
- Excuse me. Do you have an invitation?
- No.

161
00:16:22,097 --> 00:16:25,931
I mean, yes. My name is Dr. Martin Harris.
I'm on the list.

162
00:16:26,101 --> 00:16:28,262
- Let me check.
- I saw my wife go inside.

163
00:16:28,437 --> 00:16:29,802
I'm trying to find her.

164
00:16:29,972 --> 00:16:31,997
Herr Strauss?

165
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:36,108
- Dr. Martin Harris?
- Yes.

166
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:41,307
Yes. There you are. I'm Herr Strauss,
head of the Hotel Security.

167
00:16:41,483 --> 00:16:45,249
Do you have any identification?
Passport, driver's license?

168
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:47,355
No, I don't, but...

169
00:16:47,823 --> 00:16:50,815
- You would know him, he's over there.
- Professor Bressler!

170
00:16:50,993 --> 00:16:52,961
- Professor Bressler!
STRAUSS: Sir, please.

171
00:16:53,128 --> 00:16:54,789
He knows me.
He can confirm who I am.

172
00:16:54,963 --> 00:16:59,593
- Lf you will be patient, sir, no problem.
- I'm being very patient.

173
00:17:01,070 --> 00:17:05,268
Thank God. There she is. That's my wife,
over there by the buffet table.

174
00:17:09,011 --> 00:17:13,004
I have been missing for four days and she
has no idea what happened to me...

175
00:17:13,182 --> 00:17:15,776
...so I need you to take me to her
right now.

176
00:17:21,590 --> 00:17:24,115
- Okay.
- Thank you.

177
00:17:25,728 --> 00:17:28,561
- The lady in the dark dress.
- Okay.

178
00:17:29,531 --> 00:17:30,793
[GIGGLING]

179
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:32,632
Excuse me, madam.

180
00:17:34,770 --> 00:17:36,260
Your husband is here.

181
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:40,874
Liz. Oh, Jesus.

182
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:44,541
Excuse me. Do I know you?

183
00:17:48,717 --> 00:17:51,015
But, Liz... What's wrong?

184
00:17:51,587 --> 00:17:52,815
I'm sorry.

185
00:17:52,988 --> 00:17:57,357
I was in an accident. I was in a coma.
They didn't know who I was.

186
00:18:00,863 --> 00:18:02,194
I said I'm sorry.

187
00:18:03,632 --> 00:18:06,567
Oh, you must have me confused
with someone else.

188
00:18:07,903 --> 00:18:09,268
MARTIN:
Liz.

189
00:18:10,105 --> 00:18:12,767
It's me, Martin.

190
00:18:13,142 --> 00:18:14,370
Your husband.

191
00:18:17,613 --> 00:18:20,138
This is a misunderstanding.
I don't know this man.

192
00:18:20,883 --> 00:18:22,510
- Okay.
- Martin.

193
00:18:23,886 --> 00:18:25,945
This is my husband.

194
00:18:26,121 --> 00:18:28,214
You are Dr. Martin Harris?

195
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:29,516
Last time I looked.

196
00:18:30,926 --> 00:18:32,018
Yep, still me.

197
00:18:35,230 --> 00:18:38,063
What's going on here?
Is this some kind of a joke?

198
00:18:39,001 --> 00:18:40,366
Joke about what?

199
00:18:40,936 --> 00:18:43,166
Because it's not very funny.

200
00:18:43,338 --> 00:18:45,568
- Do you know this man?
- No.

201
00:18:46,642 --> 00:18:48,269
Who the hell are you?

202
00:18:49,645 --> 00:18:51,203
Who the hell are you?

203
00:18:52,981 --> 00:18:54,505
I'm her husband.

204
00:18:55,684 --> 00:18:57,379
Okay. Okay.

205
00:18:57,553 --> 00:19:00,954
Would you mind just getting him
away from us, please?

206
00:19:01,356 --> 00:19:02,880
- Liz. Liz, stop this.
MARTIN B: Hey.

207
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:05,822
- Gentlemen, please, please, please.
- Get your hands off me.

208
00:19:05,994 --> 00:19:07,427
MARTIN B: Back off.
- What's going on?

209
00:19:07,596 --> 00:19:08,688
- Tell me.
- Back off!

210
00:19:08,864 --> 00:19:11,196
- What's this all about?
MARTIN B: Why don't you take a walk?

211
00:19:11,366 --> 00:19:12,765
STRAUSS:
Gentlemen, please.

212
00:19:12,935 --> 00:19:14,766
- Don't touch me.
- Come on, come on!

213
00:19:14,970 --> 00:19:17,370
If you don't leave now,
we have to call the police.

214
00:19:17,539 --> 00:19:20,770
Call the police! Call the goddamn army!
That's a good idea!

215
00:19:20,943 --> 00:19:23,207
What's happening?
You're embarrassing me. Please.

216
00:19:23,378 --> 00:19:24,845
- Get him out of here.
- Liz!

217
00:19:25,013 --> 00:19:28,005
- I must apologize. Have a nice evening.
- I was hurt!

218
00:19:28,183 --> 00:19:30,811
- Liz! Why are you doing this to me?
MARTIN B: You okay?

219
00:19:30,986 --> 00:19:32,317
Can you believe this?

220
00:19:32,621 --> 00:19:33,747
Right there.

221
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:36,482
That's Liz. And I am...

222
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:43,659
I must've been outside.
I can't remember.

223
00:19:44,199 --> 00:19:47,498
Well, as you can see, you are not there.

224
00:19:47,703 --> 00:19:51,104
OFFICER: Immigration confirms the arrival
of a Dr. And Mrs. Harris...

225
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:54,504
...on November the 20th at 7:40 a.m.
- Yes.

226
00:19:54,676 --> 00:19:57,975
At 8:50, she checked into their suite
at the hotel...

227
00:19:58,146 --> 00:20:01,707
...followed by Dr. Harris
at 3 in the afternoon.

228
00:20:01,884 --> 00:20:04,011
- What?
- Danke.

229
00:20:04,786 --> 00:20:07,914
Wait. He's... He's not Martin Harris.

230
00:20:08,090 --> 00:20:10,854
I am Dr. Martin Harris.

231
00:20:11,026 --> 00:20:14,189
The man upstairs is pretending
to be me.

232
00:20:14,363 --> 00:20:16,627
And this impostor,
did he also steal your wife?

233
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:19,266
He must be forcing her or something.

234
00:20:19,434 --> 00:20:22,028
Well, why? Help me. Why?

235
00:20:22,204 --> 00:20:25,139
For God's sake,
just do an Internet search.

236
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:28,105
There are over 400 Martin Harrises
in the United States, sir.

237
00:20:28,277 --> 00:20:30,040
We already checked.

238
00:20:30,545 --> 00:20:34,106
Rod. Rodney Cole,
a colleague at Langemore in the States.

239
00:20:34,283 --> 00:20:36,683
A dear friend.
He can verify who I am.

240
00:20:36,852 --> 00:20:38,683
Please, call him. It's 001...

241
00:20:39,855 --> 00:20:41,482
[OFFICER DIALING]
[MARTIN SIGHS]

242
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:45,218
...508-146-2595.

243
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:50,594
RODNEY [ON RECORDING]:
This is Dr. Cole. I'm having an...

244
00:20:50,766 --> 00:20:52,131
Sorry, answering machine.

245
00:20:52,301 --> 00:20:53,393
Please, leave a message.

246
00:20:53,568 --> 00:20:56,935
Professor Bressler. Talk to him.
He's the reason I'm in Berlin.

247
00:20:57,105 --> 00:20:59,573
He invited me over to the summit
to discuss my thesis.

