Here's everything I have.

499
00:47:39,373 --> 00:47:42,103
I'll pay you in full as soon as I can.

500
00:47:45,879 --> 00:47:48,439
- For expenses.
- Sure.

501
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:51,345
I'll need 24 hours.
Call me tomorrow afternoon.

502
00:47:51,518 --> 00:47:55,648
And go find your taxi driver.
See if she'll talk to me.

503
00:47:56,089 --> 00:47:59,490
She was there at the beginning of all this.
Perhaps she knows something.

504
00:47:59,660 --> 00:48:01,287
I've already tried.

505
00:48:01,728 --> 00:48:04,720
There may be details we've overlooked.

506
00:48:05,132 --> 00:48:09,899
That's what I was really known for,
details.

507
00:48:15,742 --> 00:48:17,266
MARTIN:
Gina?

508
00:48:25,652 --> 00:48:28,212
I know why you ran away
from the accident.

509
00:48:28,922 --> 00:48:30,412
You're an illegal.

510
00:48:30,624 --> 00:48:33,855
If the police had picked you up,
they would have deported you.

511
00:48:35,429 --> 00:48:38,398
Look, I want you to have this.

512
00:48:38,565 --> 00:48:42,194
- What if I don't want it?
- It's worth at least 5000 Euro.

513
00:48:42,402 --> 00:48:44,734
Feel the weight of it.
Go on. It's the real thing.

514
00:48:48,976 --> 00:48:50,637
"E.H. To M.H."?

515
00:48:50,811 --> 00:48:56,113
Elizabeth Harris, my wife, to me, Martin.
Special gift.

516
00:48:59,419 --> 00:49:01,819
Okay, Martin Harris.
What do you want?

517
00:49:01,989 --> 00:49:03,923
There's someone
I need you to speak to.

518
00:49:04,091 --> 00:49:07,356
- I'm not talking to the police.
- He's not the police. I promise you.

519
00:49:07,527 --> 00:49:10,121
I just need you to tell him
what happened.

520
00:49:10,297 --> 00:49:12,891
Anything,
everything you can remember.

521
00:49:14,267 --> 00:49:16,792
And I need a place to crash tonight.

522
00:49:16,970 --> 00:49:18,198
[CHUCKLES]

523
00:49:21,308 --> 00:49:22,866
Please?

524
00:49:29,616 --> 00:49:33,746
Sentiment,
it's always the first thing to go.

525
00:49:35,989 --> 00:49:37,388
OFFICER [IN GERMAN]:

526
00:49:43,897 --> 00:49:45,125
Brandt.

527
00:49:48,135 --> 00:49:49,397
Jurgen?

528
00:49:56,943 --> 00:50:00,310
I picked you up from the Adlon Hotel.
You wanted to go to the airport.

529
00:50:01,448 --> 00:50:02,642
You were in a hurry.

530
00:50:02,816 --> 00:50:04,408
That's it?

531
00:50:04,851 --> 00:50:08,378
But I'd just arrived.
Doesn't make sense.

532
00:50:08,555 --> 00:50:12,514
She didn't recognize you?
How long have you been married?

533
00:50:12,693 --> 00:50:14,285
- Five years.
- Five years?

534
00:50:14,461 --> 00:50:16,952
I know it sounds crazy, but it's true.

535
00:50:17,130 --> 00:50:18,290
This is it.

536
00:50:18,832 --> 00:50:20,026
Sorry, no elevator.

537
00:50:21,368 --> 00:50:24,428
I know, not the Adlon Hotel.

538
00:50:26,573 --> 00:50:28,234
[WOMAN SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

539
00:50:31,712 --> 00:50:34,044
[NEIGHBORS SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

540
00:50:37,250 --> 00:50:41,619
The walls are made of cardboard,
but it's home.

541
00:50:42,389 --> 00:50:45,620
I have to work tonight.
You can sleep in there.

542
00:50:45,792 --> 00:50:47,521
I have extra mattress.

543
00:50:48,328 --> 00:50:49,989
MARTIN:
It's quaint.

544
00:50:52,699 --> 00:50:54,530
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

545
00:51:24,798 --> 00:51:25,924
[COUGHING]

546
00:51:36,409 --> 00:51:37,842
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

547
00:51:38,011 --> 00:51:40,206
[MAN SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

548
00:51:41,314 --> 00:51:42,440
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

549
00:51:52,425 --> 00:51:54,859
MARTIN:
Would you mind if I took a shower?

550
00:51:55,562 --> 00:51:58,053
You could try. I'm not sure you will fit.

551
00:51:58,765 --> 00:52:04,260
The light is broken. You need to leave
the door open if you want to see anything.

552
00:52:16,865 --> 00:52:18,196
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

553
00:52:19,834 --> 00:52:22,632
- I'm sorry. I just... I'm sorry.
- I give you a place to stay.

554
00:52:22,804 --> 00:52:25,398
- That does not give you the right to...
- You're right.

555
00:52:26,074 --> 00:52:28,406
They're good, the drawings.

556
00:52:42,056 --> 00:52:43,751
You want to know?

557
00:52:48,963 --> 00:52:50,362
This is me.

558
00:52:50,532 --> 00:52:53,399
Two thousand
two hundred fifty-eight Euros...

559
00:52:54,135 --> 00:52:55,602
...and counting.

560
00:52:56,304 --> 00:53:01,241
I get to 4000, I can buy papers
so I can get the hell out of here.

561
00:53:02,076 --> 00:53:04,636
Sell the watch.
You'll get more than you need.

562
00:53:04,812 --> 00:53:06,507
I plan to.

563
00:53:09,484 --> 00:53:10,917
[THUMPING]

564
00:53:12,587 --> 00:53:14,452
[NEIGHBORS MOANING
AND GRUNTING]

565
00:53:18,393 --> 00:53:19,883
[WOMAN SHOUTING]

566
00:53:20,895 --> 00:53:22,624
[MAN SHOUTING]

567
00:53:22,931 --> 00:53:24,421
[WOMAN MOANING]

568
00:53:25,700 --> 00:53:26,894
Ohh.

569
00:53:27,235 --> 00:53:28,964
How do you sleep?

570
00:53:29,170 --> 00:53:32,503
Eh. He never goes for very long.

571
00:53:34,309 --> 00:53:35,742
This guy, Jurgen.

572
00:53:35,910 --> 00:53:39,038
He's absolutely no danger to you.

573
00:53:42,283 --> 00:53:43,511
Okay.

574
00:53:43,685 --> 00:53:45,243
[KNOCKING]

575
00:53:56,431 --> 00:53:57,625
Hello.

576
00:53:58,833 --> 00:53:59,993
You got company.

577
00:54:00,168 --> 00:54:01,294
Do you have the keys?

578
00:54:01,469 --> 00:54:04,029
Bring it back to my place,
leave the keys on the TV...

579
00:54:04,205 --> 00:54:06,503
...and don't forget to reset the meter.

580
00:54:06,674 --> 00:54:09,199
- You're the best.
- I know. Come.

581
00:54:12,780 --> 00:54:15,305
Yes, I sleep with every American
you send my way.

582
00:54:15,483 --> 00:54:17,110
No need to explain.

583
00:54:17,285 --> 00:54:18,582
[BIKO LAUGHING]

584
00:54:18,820 --> 00:54:20,219
[SHOWER RUNNING]

585
00:54:35,136 --> 00:54:36,330
[KNOCKS]

586
00:54:36,504 --> 00:54:38,529
GINA:
Biko! You're going to be late.

587
00:54:38,706 --> 00:54:39,866
[GINA YELPS]

588
00:54:40,241 --> 00:54:41,606
[GINA GRUNTING]

589
00:54:43,511 --> 00:54:44,671
[GINA YELPS]

590
00:54:48,182 --> 00:54:49,615
[SHOWER RUNNING]

591
00:55:41,569 --> 00:55:42,866
[GRUNTS]

592
00:55:46,674 --> 00:55:48,198
[CLATTER]

593
00:55:55,650 --> 00:55:57,049
[SCREAMS]

594
00:56:00,521 --> 00:56:01,545
Shh.

595
00:56:02,190 --> 00:56:03,748
[CREAK]
[GLASS BREAKS]

596
00:56:06,961 --> 00:56:08,451
Jones?

597
00:56:11,766 --> 00:56:13,597
[GASPING]

598
00:56:26,013 --> 00:56:27,241
[SMITH YELLS]

599
00:56:27,415 --> 00:56:28,905
[BOTH GRUNTING]

600
00:56:43,464 --> 00:56:44,488
[SCREAMS]

601
00:56:58,746 --> 00:57:01,146
Biko? Biko?

602
00:57:11,425 --> 00:57:12,915
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

603
00:57:14,629 --> 00:57:16,153
[DOOR OPENS]
[GASPS]

604
00:57:55,236 --> 00:57:56,863
Who are you?

605
00:57:57,672 --> 00:57:59,640
Who the hell are you?

606
00:58:03,945 --> 00:58:05,412
[GINA PANTING]

607
00:58:06,781 --> 00:58:08,009
Biko's keys.

608
00:58:08,182 --> 00:58:11,242
Give them to me.
Come on, you can't stay here.

609
00:58:23,965 --> 00:58:25,557
This one!

610
00:58:30,404 --> 00:58:31,701
[CAR DOORS CLOSE]

611
00:58:39,780 --> 00:58:40,906
Are you all right?

612
00:58:42,783 --> 00:58:45,581
That guy,
he killed a nurse in the hospital.

613
00:58:45,753 --> 00:58:48,221
- What?
- He killed a nurse.